{
  "texts": [
    "With this approach, a shallow CNN was used to obtain an accuracy of 85% over the Columbia Gaze dataset.",
    "There is a plethora of research concerning the publication of eye-tracking datasets for the intensive training of ML-based solutions.",
    "The main concern of gaze prediction datasets is to cover the population with a wide range of physical features, based on different genders, ethnicities, eye color, age and accessories (e.g., glasses, makeup, etc.).",
    "Eye-tracking datasets can be classified according to the task that participants carry out during acquisition, mainly split into real-world and elicited tasks.",
    "Despite this, they do not present patterns regarding the dataset properties."
  ]
}